TY  - JOUR
AU  - Baillie, Richard T.
AU  - Bollerslev, Tim
T1  - Intra-Day and Inter-Market Volatility in Foreign Exchange Rates
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298012
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 3
SP  - 565
EP  - 585
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Four foreign exchange spot rate series, recorded on an hourly basis for a six-month period in 1986 are examined. A seasonal GARCH model is developed to describe the time-dependent volatility apparent in the percentage nominal return of each currency. Hourly patterns in volatility are found to be remarkably similar across currencies and appear to be related to the opening and closing of the worlds major markets. Robust LM tests designed to deal with the extreme leptokurtosis in the data fails to uncover any evidence of misspecification or the presence of volatility spillover effects between the currencies or across markets.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298012
ER  - 



