TY  - JOUR
AU  - Mankiw, N. Gregory
AU  - Romer, David
AU  - Shapiro, Matthew D.
T1  - Stock Market Forecastability and Volatility: A Statistical Appraisal
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298006
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 3
SP  - 455
EP  - 477
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper presents and implements statistical tests of stock market forecastability and volatility that are immune from the severe statistical problems of earlier tests. It finds that although the null hypothesis of market efficiency is rejected, the rejections are only marginal. The paper also shows how volatility tests and recent regression tests are closely related, and demonstrates that when finite sample biases are taken into account, regression tests also fail to provide strong evidence of violations of the conventional valuation model.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298006
ER  - 



