TY  - JOUR
AU  - Attanasio, Orazio P.
T1  - Risk, Time-Varying Second Moments and Market Efficiency
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298007
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 3
SP  - 479
EP  - 494
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The paper addresses two topics. First, it nests the consumption and static CAPM in a unified framework. Second, it tests for market efficiency. The first test is based on the idea that different models price risk on the basis of the covariance with different benchmark portfolios. The test of market efficiency is based on the idea that excess returns should be predictable only if risk, and therefore second moments, are predictable. The empirical results show that the static CAPM performs better than the consumption CAPM and that the former model accounts for the effects of dividend yields on expected returns.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298007
ER  - 



