AU  - Meese, Richard A.
AU  - Rose, Andrew K.
T1  - An Empirical Assessment of Non-Linearities in Models of Exchange Rate Determination
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298014
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 3
SP  - 603
EP  - 619
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper examines the empirical relation between nominal exchange rates and macroeconomic fundamentals for five major OECD countries between 1974 and 1987. Five theoretical models of exchange rate determination are considered. Potential non-linearities are examined using a variety of parametric and non-parametric techniques. We find that the poor explanatory power of the models considered cannot be attributed to non-linearities arising from time-deformation or improper functional form.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298014
ER  - 



